# ===== Waey environment variables =====
# Copy to .env.local for local overrides. All are OPTIONAL — without any of them
# the app runs fully in demo mode (chats answer offline with a demo badge).

# --- Server-side (Vercel Function api/ai.js) — set these in Vercel project settings ---
# Secret Gemini API key. Setting this single variable turns the chats live in production.
# NEVER prefix it with VITE_ or create VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY (that would expose it to the browser).
# NOTE: with the key set, chat messages (and the app's demo financial snapshot) are sent
# to Gemini through your key. The endpoint only answers as Waey (system prompts are
# server-side) and has best-effort per-IP rate limiting, but it is public — anyone using
# the deployed site consumes your credits. Add persistent rate limiting (e.g. KV) for real use.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...

# Primary and fallback models used by the proxy.
# GEMINI_FAST_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# GEMINI_FALLBACK_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# --- Client-side (baked into the bundle at build time) ---
# Where the chats send AI requests. Defaults to /api/ai (the Vercel Function).
# Only set this to point at a different proxy of your own. Direct vendor endpoints
# to known AI vendor hosts are blocked by src/lib/ai.js by design.
# VITE_AI_ENDPOINT=/api/ai
